question: Pssst. Hey. Wanted to thank you for blessing me with the amazingness that is your art. And thank you for inspiring me. Love you, hope you have a good time period. <3
answer: I’m flattered. Also your greatly welcome. I’m not good with thanking compliments I get so I apologize. I can definitely tell you that I won’t stop drawing any time soon since it’s a hobby I love too much. A kind of relaxing thing to do.

blog.name: surferofrowdybliss
blog.title: Visual Play
blog.description:
Deborah Coulter

Scissors in hand, I make collages exploring the freedom and fun of visual play. I get lost in the joy of selecting, cutting, and rearranging images. The process begins as I discover the infinite possibilities life offers through the spaciousness of an open heart. Children, animals, and nature lead the way.

I invite you to join me in these adventures of scissors & glue blending with imagination in the exquisite present.

https://instagram.com/deborahcoulterartflow/

http://society6.com/deborahcoulter

summary: ©Deborah Coulter 2019 Collage for sixth year celebration..a love for riding the waves of imagination allowing the abunDANCE to...
caption:
©Deborah Coulter 2019

Collage for sixth year celebration..a love for riding the waves of imagination allowing the abunDANCE to flow!

Visual Play turns 6 today! Thanks for following Visual Play now entering its seventh year. How fun it’s been to share my love and passion for making collages. I recently lost my Dad. Being in these waves of deep grief and acceptance after his death, I noticed my energy was in a whole different zone I had yet to experience until now. My creative channels shifted to a space of quiet and stillness. A few weeks later a surge within me to connect to beauty and joyful play came back into focus. Into the studio I went and a triptych emerged. I celebrate having this artistic groove to process the BIG feelings and allow a place to express visually my connection to life as my Dad’s ended. During our precious time together this past year with him being sick, I navigated the challenging moments by making art which kept me afloat. With immense appreciation in my heart I give thanks for my Dad’s continued joy in my choosing the life of an artist. 

I’m looking forward, with scissors and glue in hand, to continue being a surfer of rowdy bliss!!

May infinite love and peace flow…
